    public interface Parameterizer
    Generic interface for a parameterizable factory.

    To instantiate a class, use Parameterization.tryInstantiate(Class)!

    Since:
    0.4.0
    Author:
    Erich Schubert

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods Default Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method Description
      default void configure​(Parameterization config)
      Configure the class.
      java.lang.Object make()
      Make an instance after successful configuration.

    • Method Detail

      • configure

        default void configure​(Parameterization config)
        Configure the class.

        Note: the status is collected by the parameterization object, so that multiple errors may arise and be reported in one run.

        Parameters:
        config - Parameterization

      • make

        java.lang.Object make()
        Make an instance after successful configuration.

        Note: your class should return the exact type, only this very broad interface should use Object as return type.

        Returns:
        a new instance
